messages.content: Count applicants who have experience in both engineering and manager or director roles

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT r.resume_id) AS num_applicants FROM "Resume" r WHERE r.resume_id IN (SELECT e.resume_id FROM "Experience" e JOIN "JobTitle" jt ON e.job_title_id = jt.job_title_id WHERE (jt.title_name ILIKE '%engineer%') INTERSECT SELECT e.resume_id FROM "Experience" e JOIN "JobTitle" jt ON e.job_title_id = jt.job_title_id WHERE (jt.title_name ILIKE '%director%' OR jt.title_name ILIKE '%manager%'));
Find all resumes with volunteer experience
SELECT r.resume_id, r.resume_text FROM "Resume" r JOIN "Experience" e ON r.resume_id = e.resume_id WHERE e.other ILIKE '%volunteer%';
List resumes with experience in database management systems such as MySQL, PostgreSQL, Oracle, SQL Server, or MongoDB

SELECT r.resume_id, r.resume_text FROM "Resume" r JOIN "Resume_Skill" rs ON r.resume_id = rs.resume_id JOIN "Skills" s ON rs.skill_id = s.skill_id WHERE s.skill_name IN ('mysql', 'postgresql', 'oracle', 'sql server', 'mongodb');
Find all applicants with cybersecurity or network security skills

SELECT r.resume_id, r.resume_text FROM "Resume" r JOIN "Resume_Skill" rs ON r.resume_id = rs.resume_id JOIN "Skills" s ON rs.skill_id = s.skill_id WHERE s.skill_name LIKE '%cybersecurity%' OR s.skill_name LIKE '%network security%';

SELECT DISTINCT r.resume_id, r.resume_text FROM "Resume" r JOIN "Experience" e ON r.resume_id = e.resume_id JOIN "JobTitle" jt ON e.job_title_id = jt.job_title_id WHERE jt.title_name ILIKE '%software engineer%' OR jt.title_name ILIKE '%software developer%';
Get me applicants with a bachelor's degree

SELECT DISTINCT r.resume_id, r.resume_text FROM "Resume" r JOIN "Resume_College" rc ON r.resume_id = rc.resume_id JOIN "Degree" d ON rc.degree_id = d.degree_id WHERE d.degree_name ILIKE '%bachelor%' OR d.degree_name ILIKE '%b.s.%';
